Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: e6057e5ce5e11dd8be6317c96056498c9b4f09e9&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="149487" author="jay" created="Tue, 19 Apr 2016 21:47:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have a concern that the data generated by test program tend to be compressible. But I agree that shift and record size should be made default for sure.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="149451" author="adilger" created="Tue, 19 Apr 2016 18:33:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Definitely ashift and recordsize should be set. Compression maybe should be in a separate patch, but both Keith and Zhiqi reported that compression helped performance. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="149427" author="jay" created="Tue, 19 Apr 2016 16:41:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Are you proposing to turn on data compression on OSTs by default?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
